-- Chilean Stocks: Empresas Copec, Empresas La Polar, Falabella
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-01-05T20:57:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-05/chilean-stocks-empresas-copec-empresas-la-polar-falabella.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Santiago.  The Ipsa index fell 0.2 percent to 4,188.65. The  MSCI Chile (MXCL) 
index increased 0.1 percent to 2,309.54.  Empresas Copec SA (COPEC)  (COPEC CC) fell 0.7 percent to 6,841.1
pesos. Chile’s largest forestry company and fuel distributor
said it will invest $1 billion in 2012, according to a
presentation posted on its website. This compares with $1.1
billion it planned to invest in 2011, according to a previous
presentation.  The company’s forestry unit, Celulosa Arauco & Constitucion
SA, sold $500 million of 10-year notes yesterday. Moody’s cut
the unit’s outlook to negative from stable.  Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)  (LAPOLAR CC) declined 6.7 percent to a
record low 234.7 pesos. The department store operator that filed
for bankruptcy protection in 2011 has plunged 19 percent in the
past four days since being dropped from the  Ipsa (IPSA)  benchmark
index.  SACI Falabella (FALAB)  (FALAB CC) rose 0.4 percent to 4,137.8
pesos. The country’s largest retailer by market value plans to
invest $3.34 billion by 2015 to open 204 new stores and 16
malls, of which $888 million will be invested in 2012, according
to a presentation on the company’s website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
